TITLE: White House and Republicans reach a tentative deal to avoid U.S. default
SUMMARY: House Republicans have reached a tentative deal with the White House to address the nation's debt ceiling and avoid a default.

TITLE: Treasury now says it could run out of money June 5, buying time for debt ceiling talks
SUMMARY: Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen said Friday that the United States will likely have enough reserves to push off a potential debt default until June 5.

SUMMARY: Disney urged a federal court to reject a request by Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis to disqualify the judge overseeing the company's lawsuit against the governor.
